# Atheon AI Production Secrets Example
# This file serves as documentation of required secrets.
# In production, all secrets are managed using Doppler.
#
# To use with Doppler CLI: doppler run -- kubectl apply -k .
#
# The following variables should be configured in your Doppler project:

# API Keys for LLM Services
# OPENAI_API_KEY
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
# HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY

# Authentication
# JWT_SECRET_KEY (used as JWT_SECRET in application)
# JWT_ALGORITHM
# JWT_REFRESH_SECRET

# External Services
# KAFKA_USERNAME
# KAFKA_PASSWORD
# KAFKA_SSL_CERT
# KAFKA_SSL_KEY

# Database
# DATABASE_URL (or individual components)

# Monitoring
# OPENTELEMETRY_API_KEY
# GRAFANA_API_KEY
# PROMETHEUS_AUTH_TOKEN
# ELK_STACK_PASSWORD

# Feature Flags
# FEATURE_FLAGS (JSON containing ENABLE_HITL, ENABLE_ADVANCED_LOGGING, etc.)

# Log Level
# LOG_LEVEL

# IMPORTANT: Never commit actual secrets to Git - use Doppler for all environments.